last_episode_to_air.name: Global Warming. A Big Conspiracy?
last_episode_to_air.overview: Earth has faced changes in climate before, so is global warming as alarming as people think? The team tries to educate a special guest on the issue.

name: Mystery Lab
overview: Host Felipe Castanhari explores science, history, mysteries and marvels, uncovering mind-blowing facts with help from his lab buddies.

episodes.name: The Mysteries of the Bermuda Triangle
episodes.overview: With Dr. Tay and AI assistant Briggs, Felipe makes sense of the mythical region linked to unexplained disappearances of airplanes and ships.

episodes.name: The 20 Million Deaths Caused by the Great Plague
episodes.overview: Entire cities decimated. Twenty million dead. The origin of quarantine. The crew investigates how the plague swept across Europe during the Middle Ages.

episodes.name: Learning How to Time Travel
episodes.overview: What is space-time bending? How does it connect to gravity? Felipe takes a closer look at the science behind time travel.

episodes.name: From Wolf to Dog
episodes.overview: As Felipe visits the Shy Wolf Sanctuary, he examines how — thousands of years ago — certain wolves evolved into dogs and became closer to humans.

episodes.name: Zombie Apocalypse. What if it was real?
episodes.overview: Felipe talks about flesh-eating creatures that are stranger than fiction, while the impressionable Betinho frets about an experiment at Dr. Tay's lab.

episodes.name: The Great Extinction
episodes.overview: Could humans be wiped out from the planet like the dinosaurs? Is life on Earth facing another mass extinction? The lab crew investigates.

episodes.name: The Path to Artificial Superintelligence
episodes.overview: Super-intelligent computers are not too far away, but will society be able to keep up with these advances? Could AI — like Briggs — turn against us?
